TY  - JOUR
T1  - Monitoring an Input-Output Model for Production. I. The Control Charts
AU  - Jensen, D. R.
AU  - Hui, Y. V.
AU  - Ghare, P. M.
Y1  - 1984/10/01
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.30.10.1197
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.30.10.1197
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1197
EP  - 1206
VL  - 30
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Control charts are given for monitoring an input-output model against changes in form, against changes in its coefficients, and against changes in process variance. When a process is not in control due to changes in some coefficients, monitoring shifts to a diagnostic mode to identify the altered coefficients and thus the needed adjustments to the process. Control limits from special aid tables are used; these are considered along with the choice of design. Operating characteristics of the charts are summarized under standard assumptions.
AB  - Control charts are given for monitoring an input-output model against changes in form, against changes in its coefficients, and against changes in process variance. When a process is not in control due to changes in some coefficients, monitoring shifts to a diagnostic mode to identify the altered coefficients and thus the needed adjustments to the process. Control limits from special aid tables are used; these are considered along with the choice of design. Operating characteristics of the charts are summarized under standard assumptions.
